<body class="bg-white">
    <%- include("../partials/header") %>

        <main class="py-8 bg-white">
            <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                    <article class="lg:col-span-2">
                        <div class="bg-white">
                            <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">
                                <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home</a>
                                <span class="mx-2">></span>
                                <a href="/home-improvement" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home
                                    Improvement</a>
                                <span class="mx-2">></span>
                                <span class="text-gray-800">Bathroom Remodel Guide</span>
                            </nav>

                            <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 leading-tight">
                                Bathroom Remodel Guide: Planning, Costs, and Smart Upgrades
                            </h1>

                            <div class="mb-8">
                                <img src="/images/bathroom-remodel-guide.webp"
                                    alt="Beautifully remodeled modern bathroom"
                                    class="w-full h-80 object-cover rounded-lg shadow-lg" fetchpriority="high">
                            </div>

                            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
                                <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                                    A bathroom remodel is one of the best home improvement projects because it improves
                                    comfort, adds daily convenience, and can increase your home’s value. Whether your
                                    bathroom is outdated, too small, or simply not functional, upgrading it can
                                    completely change how your home feels.
                                </p>

                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    The key to a successful remodel is planning everything before you start. From layout
                                    decisions to materials and budgeting, small choices can make a big difference in the
                                    final result. This guide will help you remodel confidently with practical tips and
                                    modern ideas that work for most homes.
                                </p>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Why a Bathroom Remodel Is a Smart
                                    Home Upgrade</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    Bathrooms are high-traffic spaces, which means they wear out faster than many other
                                    rooms. Old tiles crack, paint peels due to moisture, and fixtures lose their shine.
                                    A remodeling project solves these issues while also making your bathroom more
                                    efficient and attractive.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    A well-designed bathroom also improves hygiene and safety. Better ventilation
                                    reduces humidity, slip-resistant flooring prevents accidents, and updated plumbing
                                    lowers the risk of leaks. Most importantly, a bathroom upgrade can make your
                                    everyday routine easier and more relaxing.
                                </p>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Bathroom Remodel Planning: What
                                    to Decide First</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    Before buying tiles or fixtures, you should know your goals. Some people remodel for
                                    better looks, while others need more storage, better lighting, or a more spacious
                                    layout.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    Start by asking yourself what matters most. Are you upgrading a small guest
                                    bathroom, or doing a full master bathroom renovation? Once your priorities are
                                    clear, it becomes easier to plan your budget and pick the right design.
                                </p>

                                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-3">Define Your Budget Range</h3>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    Your budget will control many decisions, including tile quality, vanity style,
                                    shower type, and even labor costs. A small cosmetic upgrade can cost much less than
                                    a full tear-out remodel.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    If you want to avoid overspending, always keep extra money reserved for hidden
                                    problems. Bathrooms often reveal issues like old plumbing, water damage, or uneven
                                    floors once demolition begins.
                                </p>

                                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-3">Decide if You’re Changing the
                                    Layout</h3>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    Keeping the same layout usually reduces cost and saves time. Moving the toilet,
                                    shower, or sink requires plumbing changes, which increases labor and material costs.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    If your bathroom feels too tight or poorly designed, a layout change may be worth
                                    it. However, for many homeowners, simply upgrading finishes and storage can improve
                                    the space without major reconstruction.
                                </p>

                                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-3">Choose Your Bathroom Style Theme
                                </h3>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    A consistent theme makes the remodel look more professional and well-designed.
                                    Popular bathroom styles include modern, minimalist, classic, and spa-inspired.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    You don’t need luxury materials to get a premium look. Even basic upgrades, like
                                    matching hardware finishes and choosing a balanced color palette, can make your
                                    bathroom feel high-end.
                                </p>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Best Bathroom Remodel Ideas for a
                                    Modern Look</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    A modern bathroom focuses on clean lines, easy maintenance, and comfort. Even small
                                    changes can make your space feel fresh and updated.
                                </p>

                                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-3">Upgrade Your Vanity and Storage
                                </h3>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    A vanity is often the main focus of the bathroom. A stylish vanity instantly
                                    improves the look of the entire room while also adding useful storage.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    If your bathroom is small, consider a wall-mounted vanity. It creates more visual
                                    space and makes cleaning the floor easier. You can also add floating shelves or a
                                    mirrored cabinet to store daily items neatly.
                                </p>

                                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-3">Improve Lighting for Function and
                                    Beauty</h3>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    Lighting can make or break a bathroom design. A well-lit bathroom feels cleaner,
                                    brighter, and more modern. It also helps with grooming tasks like shaving or
                                    applying makeup.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    For better results, use layered lighting. One light is not enough for most
                                    bathrooms. You should have overhead lighting, mirror lighting, and soft lighting
                                    options if possible.
                                </p>

                                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-3">Choose Durable and Water-Resistant
                                    Materials</h3>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    Bathrooms deal with constant moisture, so material selection matters. Floors, walls,
                                    and cabinetry should handle humidity without swelling or cracking.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    Porcelain tiles are a popular choice because they are durable and easy to clean.
                                    Waterproof paint and moisture-resistant drywall also help protect the room and
                                    prevent long-term damage.
                                </p>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Bathroom Remodel Costs: What
                                    Affects the Price?</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    The cost of remodeling depends on many factors, and it can vary based on your
                                    location and the quality of materials. A minor remodel is usually more affordable,
                                    while a complete renovation with plumbing changes can be much more expensive.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">The biggest cost factors usually include labor,
                                    waterproofing, tile work, fixtures, and cabinetry. Custom showers and premium
                                    materials also increase the final price. Planning your spending early prevents
                                    surprises later.</p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Here are common cost areas where budgets often increase:
                                </p>
                                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
                                    <li>Tile work and waterproofing labor</li>
                                    <li>New plumbing and fixture upgrades</li>
                                    <li>Vanity, storage, and mirror replacements</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    If you stay focused on key upgrades, you can complete a stylish bathroom remodel
                                    even without a luxury budget.
                                </p>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Bathroom Remodel Checklist for a
                                    Smooth Project</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    A remodel becomes stressful when steps are missed. A simple plan keeps everything
                                    organized and helps you avoid delays.
                                </p>

                                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-3">Step 1: Measure and Plan the
                                    Layout</h3>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    Accurate measurements help you choose the correct vanity size, shower type, and
                                    storage solutions. Measuring also prevents ordering the wrong materials.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    If you are unsure, creating a simple sketch or digital plan helps you see where
                                    everything fits before making purchases.
                                </p>

                                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-3">Step 2: Choose Fixtures and
                                    Finishes Early</h3>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    Fixtures should match your bathroom theme. This includes faucets, showerheads, towel
                                    bars, and cabinet handles. Choosing them early prevents you from mixing styles
                                    later.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    It also helps to choose your tile and paint colors early, because lighting and
                                    finishes should work well together.
                                </p>

                                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-3">Step 3: Focus on Ventilation and
                                    Waterproofing</h3>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    Ventilation is one of the most important parts of a bathroom upgrade. A strong
                                    exhaust fan removes moisture and prevents mold growth. Waterproofing protects your
                                    walls and floors from long-term damage.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    If your bathroom has weak airflow, even expensive tiles will not last as long. A
                                    good ventilation system keeps everything fresh and dry.
                                </p>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Small Bathroom Remodel Tips for
                                    Tight Spaces</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    Small bathrooms can feel bigger with the right design choices. You don’t always need
                                    more square footage to create a spacious feel.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    Using light colors, large mirrors, and clear shower glass can instantly open the
                                    room visually. Floating vanities and compact storage solutions also keep the floor
                                    clear and reduce clutter. Even changing the door to a sliding style can save space
                                    in certain layouts.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    A smart small-space design can make a bathroom remodel feel like a major upgrade
                                    without major construction.
                                </p>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Common Bathroom Remodel Mistakes
                                    to Avoid</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    Many remodeling problems happen because people rush decisions or ignore practical
                                    needs. Avoiding common mistakes can save money and prevent repair issues.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    A common mistake is choosing stylish materials that are hard to maintain. Another
                                    issue is installing poor-quality waterproofing, which can cause leaks behind tiles.
                                    Some people also forget storage planning, which leads to clutter and poor
                                    organization.
                                </p>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
                                    Also, never ignore the importance of proper slope in the shower floor and correct
                                    placement of drains. These details determine whether your bathroom functions well
                                    long-term.
                                </p>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Conclusion</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700">
                                    A bathroom remodel is one of the most valuable upgrades you can make in your home.
                                    It improves daily comfort, increases functionality, and gives your space a clean and
                                    modern feel. With good planning, smart material choices, and the right upgrades, you
                                    can create a bathroom that looks great and lasts for years.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </article>

